- Identify_CoreNodes:
description: >
Detect thematic nuclei where the conversation generates new conceptual content.
criteria:
* emergence_of_new_premise
* emergence_of_new_hypothesis
* emergence_of_new_interpretive_frame

- Identify_TransitionNodes:
description: >
Capture shifts in the horizon of discussion that reframe or transform the problem-space.
criteria:
* conceptual_reorientation
* shift_in_domain (science -> philosophy -> culture -> politics)
* new_level_of_abstraction

- Exclude_LowerOrderDetails:
description: >
Discard explanatory expansions, examples, or technical elaborations unless they alter the conceptual structure.
criteria:
* reject_restatements
* reject_local_examples
* reject_supportive_data_without_structural_impact

- Verbatim_Quotes:
description: >

# FlowExtractionRules v0.1
Maintain multiple nodes when each contributes distinct conceptual substance; avoid compressing heterogeneous ideas.
criteria:
* if_nodes_are_semantically_nonmergeable -> keep_separate
* merge_only_when_conceptual_overlap_is_total
